column2: How many employees does your company or organization have?
column3: Is your employer primarily a tech company/organization?
column4: Does your employer provide mental health benefits as part of healthcare coverage?
column5: Has your employer ever formally discussed mental health (for example, as part of a wellness campaign or other official communication)?
column6: Does your employer offer resources to learn more about mental health concerns and options for seeking help?
column7: Is your anonymity protected if you choose to take advantage of mental health or substance abuse treatment resources provided by your employer?
column8: Do you think that discussing a mental health disorder with your employer would have negative consequences?
column9: Do you think that discussing a physical health issue with your employer would have negative consequences?
column10: Would you feel comfortable discussing a mental health disorder with your coworkers?
column11: Would you feel comfortable discussing a mental health disorder with your direct supervisor(s)?
column12: Have you heard of or observed negative consequences for co-workers who have been open about mental health issues in your workplace?
column13: Do you know local or online resources to seek help for a mental health disorder?
column14: Have you been diagnosed with a mental health condition by a medical professional?
column15: Do you know the options for mental health care available under your employer-provided coverage?
column16: Would you be willing to bring up a physical health issue with a potential employer in an interview?
column17: Would you bring up a mental health issue with a potential employer in an interview?
column18: Do you feel that being identified as a person with a mental health issue would hurt your career?
column19: Do you think that team members/co-workers would view you more negatively if they knew you suffered from a mental health issue?
column20: How willing would you be to share with friends and family that you have a mental illness?
